text: Eudonia protorthra is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1885. It is found in Australia, where it has been recorded from New South Wales, Queensland and Victoria. == Description == The wingspan is about 20 mm. There is a grey pattern on the forewings, with a broad ragged white band across the wing. The larvae feed on mosses. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1885 Category:Scopariinae
title: Eudonia protorthra
